Former PSL assistant referee of the season Shaun Olive is pleading for donations. JOHANNESBURG - Former PSL assistant referee of the season Shaun Olive is pleading for donations for treatment after he was involved in a car accident on Tuesday. The assistant referee requires funds before he can undergo the necessary surgery procedures following his freak accident. Olive has been a standard feature in local season over recent years. He was crowned the 2019/20 Premier Soccer League Assistant Referee of the Season. Olive has already acted as either a first assistant or a fourth official in over 40 matches in both the DStv Premiership and GladAfrica Championship so far this season.